==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*kunjan'', from Indo-European ''*gen-'' ‘produce’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[kin]], Old Saxon [[kunni]] (Dutch [[kunne]]), Old High German [[kunni]], Old Norse [[kyn]], Gothic [[𐌺𐌿𐌽𐌹]].  The IE root is also the source of Greek [[γένος]], Latin [[genus#Latin|genus]].

